  <div class="notes-grid">
    <div class="note-card">
      <h4>.pbip vs .pbix</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>.pbix is binary — Git stores it but you can't diff it meaningfully</li>
        <li>.pbip splits into JSON files — every DAX change is readable in a PR</li>
        <li>Both open identically in Power BI Desktop</li>
        <li>Enable via Preview Features — stable as of late 2024</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="note-card">
      <h4>Azure DevOps REST Publish</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Use Service Principal (not personal account) for pipeline auth</li>
        <li>Grant SP "Member" role on target workspace</li>
        <li>PowerShell: Import-PowerBIFile or REST POST /imports</li>
        <li>Free tier covers up to 5 users and unlimited private repos</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="note-card">
      <h4>Branching Strategy</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>main branch = production-ready, protected (require PR)</li>
        <li>dev branch = active development, published to workspace</li>
        <li>Scale to Dev + Prod: dev branch → Dev workspace, main → Prod workspace</li>
        <li>Tag releases: v1.0, v1.1 for audit trail</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
